This paper is about a recommendation system using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a dual attentions mechanism, which is a type of attention mechanism commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper deals with data sparsity, which is a common problem in Recommender Systems (cs.SI) research. Finally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to process textual data, which is a topic in Computational Linguistics (cs.CL).
